# Proc Macros 

I learned all to late in my own journey through proc-macro land that there is a proper way to do proc_macros using syn and quote.
Understanding these libraries is equivalent to knowing how to write proc macros so I'll start out by going into depth on them.
Before anything else though, you'll need to start a new crate (or two) and put this in the cargo.toml of the one you intend to write proc_macros in.

For clarity's sake the folder structure im working with is   
    macros   
    macros/macros/cargo.toml  //where we did macro_rules!
    macros/proc-macros/cargo.toml  //new
    macros/deriveable_traits //new 


<CodeSnippet>
```toml
    [lib]
    proc-macro = true
    [dependencies]
    syn = "2.0"
    quote = "1.0"
```
</CodeSnippet>

Proc macros cant be used in the crate theyre defined in, and the traits they implement derives for can't be in the same crate they are in.

